         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot Garden ¶ 2/5/71 ¶  ¶ It will afford me much pleasure, dear Mr Purchas, to supply you with such young pines and other plants, as the reduced means of my department allow me to furnish. ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.05.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Albert Purchas</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Letter book B, no. 73, Melbourne General Cemetery.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Purchas: 'Read 10-5-71'. M's letter was read at a meeting of the Trustees held on 13 September 1871 (Minute book 1).</p>
               </note>Melbourne bot Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2/5/71</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It will afford me much pleasure, dear Mr Purchas, to supply you with such young pines and other plants, as the reduced means of my department allow me to furnish.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See A. Purchas to M, 27 April 1871.</p>
               </note> Be so good to prepare the ground at once and let your gardener bring a sketch of the ground when he comes for the plants.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
